</p><p>Significant (p&#x0003c;0.05) decrease in SBP, DBP, MBP, total and indexed LVM values were observed in all the groups at the end of treatment compared to baseline values. In all groups no significant changes in biochemical measurements and in the remaining echocardiographic parameters were found at the end of treatment (<xref ref-type="table" rid="T1">Tabs. I</xref>, <xref ref-type="table" rid="T2">II</xref>). <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F2">Figure 2</xref> shows the responses of LVM/h<sup>2.7</sup> values of individuals to the three treatments.</p><p>
